        i'm aware that this conversation is being had in the comments about the mad amount of old songs in the chart but i got a bit passionate typing a reply so i'll post it as it's own comment:

        the OCC need to just bring in recurrency rules like billboard!! they got that right because it's obvious that streaming gives older songs a huge advantage. songs have always stood the test of time but they didn't use to clog up the charts, it's just that people can now go stream whatever song comes to mind. it's not an accurate reflection of what's popular if it's a song that's already been popular on the charts. the singles chart would be such a better reflection of the contemporary if they had songs go 'recurrent' (out) after dropping below #50 after 20 weeks charting. rather than booting songs down the chart on the 10th week? which destroys songs that aren't mega popular's success and only halves the songs that are mega popular, causing them to stay forever anyway?

        billboard has a lot of funny rules which the OCC do better, but ACR is an obvious mess. i hope they fix this, otherwise every 'end of year' chart will be worse than the next
